Honey Apple Butter
  --Cara Peterson and Alon Shaya

1 c apple cider
1/2 c oj
1 lb apples, peeled, cored, and roughly chopped
1/4 c honey
1 tsp kosher salt
1 1/2 tbsp dark brown sugar

1/2 tsp orange blossom honey
1 tsp baharat (or pumpkin pie spice)

Place cider, oj, apples, honey, salt, and sugar in a sauce pot and bring to simmer. Cover and cook at a simmer, stirring frequently for 1 1/2-2 hrs. Place the contents in a food processor and blend until smooth. Put the mixture back in the pot. Add the honey and baharat. Bring back to a simmer and cook until thickened. Chill before serving.
